Another winner to go into my arsenal. I made this pretty much as indicated but left out the ground meat (didn't have any) and used one lb of medium sausage. I also left out the carrots and celery (not making chicken soup here). I cooked the sausage and then scooped it out and cooked the onions in the sausage fat with a bit more olive oil. Then I continued the recipe as indicated and came up with a beautiful THICK ragout that was to die for. I didn't have any elbow macarroni so I used those tiny bow ties (about 3/4 cup). The starch from the pasta was wonderful and made the broth nice and thick. It gets a big thumbs up.

