Rating: 4
A great and versatile soup. I eliminated the ground beef and increased the sausages to 5. Garbanzo instead of the cannellini beans worked great and, because we love pasta, I increased the chicken broth to 48 oz and used a full cup of macaroni. Also, two tablespoons of dried basil replaced the fresh. This has become a staple in my kitchen, a great "go-to". And it's even better the second day.

Rating: 3
I found this to be quite good and very Italian. After reading some of the reviews, I was concerned about this turning out as a soup, which was not my goal. To minimize liquid, I strained off the sausage liquid once browned and strained the beans. I also almost doubled the macaroni so as to absorb more liquid, but also provide a greater amount of pasta as I though 1/2 cup seemed like a very small amount. I also boiled the mixture at a little higher heat to ensure some of the excess liquid boiled off. The results was a perfect consistency and is best served in a pasta or soup bowl. The downside to not using ground beef was that the end results was quite piquant (which most of my dinner guests preferred). Next time I think I will cut the sausage volume down by 25%, double the cannellini and increase the amount of tomatoes by 50%. I'll consider throwing in a little balsamic vinegar for a little tang. My teenage daughter called this Italian chili - maybe so! Very, very flavorful - gourmet comfort food.

